package.json 
> first file in the application
> entry point
> contains meta data
> packages
> scripts

/////Step to generate package.json ////
**NodeJs must be installed
> navigate to the folder
> npm init
> answer all questions
> type yes

/////////////////////////
how to install package
generate react app 

///////Step to install packages/////////
**NodeJs must be installed
> navigate to the folder
> npm i packagename /npm install packagename

///////dev Dependency//////////////
npm i jest --save-dev


//////////////////////
Generate React App
//////////////////////
#window
**One Time**
> open cmd as admin
> npm i -g create-react-app

**Next All Time**
> open cmd
> go inside folder
> create-react-app appname

#Mac/Linux
**One Time**
> open terminal
> sudo npm i -g create-react-app

**Next All Time**
> open cmd
> go inside folder
> create-react-app appname

//////////////////////
Run React App
//////////////////////
> go inside the folder 
> npm start
> http://localhost:3000


component
> functional component
  # dumb component
  # use for display purpose
  # light in weight
  # cannot maintain state

> class component
  # Logical component
  # Heavy in weight
  # use for display, api call and data interaction
  # Can maintain state
